column168: UPON TRANSFER OF THE GOODS FROM AN INBOUND TRUCK INTO OUR WAREHOUSE FACILIT Y, THE CYLINDER OF DANGEROPUS GOODS FELL OFF THE SKID AND ROLLED UNDER THE WHEEL OF THE FORKLIFT. THE CYLINDER BURST AND THE LIQUID SPILLED ONTO THE F LOOR IN AN APPROXIMATE 24 INCH AREA. A CALL WAS PLACED TO AIRPORT EMERGENCY TO ADVISE OF THE SPILL AND TO CHEMTREC FOR TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. A CALL WA S THEN PLACED TO I.T. CORP FOR THE CHEMICAL CLEAN UP AND REMOVAL. AS A PREC AUTION THE FACILITIES WERE EVACUATED UNTIL A REP FROM THE I.T. CORP ADVISED THE AREA WAS SAFE TO WORK AROUND. THE TWO AGENTS IN THE WAREHOUSE, AFTER A SHOWER AND CHANGE OF CLOTHES, WERE TAKEN TO A HOSPITAL FOR A CHECK UP AND FOUND UNHARMED. THE SPILLED CONTENTS WERE CLEANED UP AND REMOVED FROM THE A REA BY I.T. CORP.  TO PREVENT FUTURE INCIDENTS, A REVIEW OF OUR ACCEPTANCE, HANDLING AND STOWAGE WILL BE DISCUSSED WITH THOSE INDIVIDUALS THAT COME IN CONTACT WITH THESE TYPE OF GOODS.
